DC-9-31
Evacuation
Procedures
Bracing
Position
Both front doors and the
tail exit are equiped with
inflatable evacuation slides.
You are flying aboard a DC-9-31 with a skilled and
experienced crew who are thoroughly trained to cope
with and handle any emergency situation.
While aircraft emergencies are infrequent, procedures
have been established as precautionary measures.
To
acquaint you with these
safety features of this
procedures
and with the
aircraft, we
ask that you
familiarize yourself with the information provided on
this card.
In the event of an emergency, remain calm. Listen and
follow carefully the instructions given by your Flight
Attendant or other crew members.
Seat Belts
Seat belts are provided for your safety and comfort.
They must be
fastened
securely
while taxiing and
during takeoffs and landings. It is recommended that
your seat belt be fastened at any time you are seated.
Seat Backs
Seat backs must be in the upright position during all
takeoffs and landings.
Smoking
Whenever the "No Smoking" sign is on, all smoking
material must be extinguished.
Flotation Equipment
Your DC-9 is equiped with flotation seat cushions in
the
event
of
an
emergency
Water
landing.
Life
preservers, life rafts and other overwater equipment
are
carried
on
those
flights invelved
in extended
overwater operations.
Tail Exit
Al) 00000000000000000002
00000000000000000000
00000000000
Rear Evacuation Route
Open the rear cabin door and eject
the tail cone.
The evacuation slide
will automatically inflate.
DOOR EXITS
SALIDA POR LAS PUERTAS
Door Operation
Rotate handle in the direction of
arrow to "Open". Push out on door
and pull red handle on floor to
inflate evacuation slide.
Evacuation Slide
Remove high heel
shoes.
Sit on
door sill and push off, feet first. Do
not hold onto sides of slide and in
no instance jump onto it.
EXIT!
1000
000
Oxygen System
The oxygen compartment will open automatically if needed.
Should the compartment open, pull the nearest mask to your
face and place it over your nose and mouth. Adjust the head
band and breathe normally. Wear the mask until advised by the
crew to remove it.
Window Exit Operation
Insert hand in slot and pull handle
down.
Grasp
window at top and
bottom and lift inward.
